%I A396786 #27 Jun 24 2026 19:52:42
%S A396786 3,17,199,22051,387199,52246349
%N A396786 Smallest prime p such that p^(q^3) = +-1 mod q^5 is true when q is any of the first n primes.
%H A396786 Rhys Feltman, <a href="/A396786/a396786.txt">Python code</a>
%e A396786 a(1) = 3 because 3^(2^3) mod 2^5 = +-1: 3^8 = 6561. 6561 = 205*32 (6560) + 1. Prime 2 obviously does not work because 2^m mod 2^n will always be either 0 or 2^m.
%o A396786 (PARI) isok(p, vp) = for (i=1, #vp, my(q=vp[i], q5=q^5, m=Mod(p, q5)^q^3); if ((m != Mod(1, q5)) && (m != Mod(-1, q5)), return(0));); 1;
%o A396786 a(n) = my(p=2, vp=primes(n)); while (!isok(p, vp), p=nextprime(p+1)); p; \\ _Michel Marcus_, Jun 13 2026
%Y A396786 Cf. A395587 (with q^2 instead of q^3).
%K A396786 nonn,more
%O A396786 1,1
%A A396786 _Rhys Feltman_, Jun 05 2026
%E A396786 a(6) from _Michel Marcus_, Jun 13 2026
